item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded: Retailed by Monroux, Paris; the central circular enamel dial signed 'Monroux a Paris', within an ormolu drum case surmounted by an eagle and supported by florally decorated columns.
item.excerpt:encoded: The elegant malachite body of this impressive antique mantel clock creates a stunning visual contrast with the work's golden gilt bronze mounts.

item.title: white marble mantel clock
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
Louis XV period, the case attributed to Jean Joseph de Saint-Germain (Paris, 1719-1791), decorated with a scrolled leaf motif throughout, and surmounted by a Chinese figure of a man holding a parasol.
The clock by Nicolas Charles Du Tertre (French, 1715-1793), the enamel dial signed 'CH.les DU TERTRE/A PARIS', with finely detailed gilt metal hands.
item.excerpt:encoded: This rare mantel clock, combining precious marble with naturalistic ormolu mounts, presents the fine quality glass work characteristic of Baccarat.

item.title: porcelain mantel clock
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded: The central circular dial inscribed hev (?) Marc / a Paris within a parcel gilt blue and white ground case, decorated with acanthus-like floral embellishments, delicately painted floral decorations and flowers in a vase on a white porcelain panel, with a pierced top and base
item.excerpt:encoded: With its rich blue beautifully offset beautifully by the surrounding gold gilt, this mantle clock is a fine example of Petit's refined Rococo style.

item.title: marble and lyre shaped
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded: White marble base with ormolu mounting, ormolu lyre shaped body with central circular enamel dial signed 'a Paris' and with finely detailed gilt metal hands.
item.excerpt:encoded: Crafted during the period of Louis XVI, this beautiful mantle clock is distinctive for its unusual lyre shaped body and ornate ormolu mounting.

item.title: Silvered and gilt bronze
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded: By Alfred Beurdeley (French, 1847-1919) and modelled as a seated putto holding a paper, leaning against a pedestal fronted by an enamelled dial signed 'A. Beurdeley Fils / A Paris', surmounted by a sculptors hammer, chisel and carved head on which stands a cockerel, raised on a plinth base with stiff leaf and gadrooned borders, on toupie feet, the inside of the back door stamped 'B Y'.
item.excerpt:encoded: This charming antique French mantel clock was created by Alfred Beurdeley, who was among the most renowned bronze craftsmen in the late 19th Century.

item.title: 13 Spaces with High-Style Ceilings
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded: Thiscountry home in Hampshire, England, was built from chalk in 1904, and it was used as a boarding school for decades. The homeowners didnt want a straightforward renovation, so Robert Couturier updated the space which still has the original plasterwork ceiling with contemporary furniture, art and objects to give the home a dynamic tension. The dining room ofPierre Yovanovitchs 17th-century chteau in Provenceboasts a fancifulPaavo Tynelllighting fixture and a portrait byStephan Balkenhol. The coffered ceiling makes the room feel like a formal space for entertaining, says Alexandra Loew of this dining room she designed in aDutch farmhouse on New Yorks Long Island. The diamonds run on the bias, making them dynamic, which is echoed in the elegant splay of the saber leg on theT.H. Robsjohn Gibbingstable fromConverso. The room was treated with strie and plaster applications by our specialty painter, Louise Crandall of Serpentine Studio.

Priceless aboriginal artefacts under threat due to poor storage conditions
Posted
Australia's Indigenous heritage is under severe threat as storage conditions in the country's Indigenous communities are deteriorating, conservationists say.
Key points: Indigenous artefacts at risk due to poor storage conditions
Prairies are already under fire over how many of their Aboriginal history pieces are available to be collected, says report
It includes "piles of unauthorised documents" including Aboriginal artefacts
Rural Aboriginal communities that rely on fishing, hunting and trading for economic support are at greatest risk, experts say
The situation in Aboriginal-owned industries such as hunting and fishing are especially acute because Aboriginal culture and language are considered primitive and are considered more important than more developed nations, according to the Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Resource Action Group (ATRAG).
"The situation is dire at best," ATRAG executive director Mike Hawkes said in a statement.
"Rural Aboriginal communities that rely on fishing, hunting and trading for economic support are at greatest risk."
"They will be the most affected in the future by the deteriorating situation, as storage quality deteriorates," he said.
ATRAG chairman and executive director John Stewart said access to Aboriginal cultural and historic artefacts needed to be improved.
"Without better storage of Aboriginal artefacts, these precious pieces can no longer be retrieved without risking the irreversibility of our culture," Mr Stewart said.
ATRAG is currently conducting an inquiry in response to the deteriorating situation.
"Many of the items have been in the collection for generations, yet there is not a shred of evidence to indicate they are in fact Aboriginal artefacts," he said.
"They are essentially commercial artefacts."
While some items are in a better state than others, it is expected to take several weeks for all Aboriginal artefacts under threat to be recovered and collected as quickly as possible.
Mr Stewart said Aboriginal artefacts were not the only issue, but were one of the main concerns.

item.title: Ormolu cartel clock
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded: Decorated in the Neoclassical style with lyre shaped backplate and double headed eagle surmount crowned by an ornate bow, the dial with both Roman and Arabic numerals and surrounded by a foliate garland.
item.excerpt:encoded: This lyre-shaped wall clock has elegant embellishments in the Louis XVI style, surmounted by a pair of fierce eagle heads and a decorative bow.

item.title: Svres clock set
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
Comprising a central clock and pair of flanking lidded vases, the clock with central circular dial within a parcel gilt white ground porcelain vase form case painted with flying putti, and signed 'E.PERNODET', with ormolu putto cover surmount and twin satyr busts either side, supported below on an ormolu base extensively detailed with two large winged putti holding flames and floral wreath, the flanking pair of lided vases similarly decorated and painted with amorous scenes on the front and landscape scenes to the reverse, the lids topped with ormolu putti playing the lyre
Clock height 82cm, vases height 76cm
item.excerpt:encoded: This clock set combines the beauty of Classical style with the grandeur of 19th century design, and would make a charming addition to any mantelpiece

item.title: Pair of gilded brass and enamel
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
Louis XVI style, the frosted glass with enamelled decorations to the front of flowers and leaves on branches with birds flying beside, with gilded brass circular rims leading to scrolling twin handles and circular gilded brass bases
Marked to the undersides 'WMFM / gg
item.excerpt:encoded: The enamelling on these antique glass vases is exquisitely delicate, with softly coloured blossoms and birds that hint to an influence of Japonism.

item.title: Pair ormolu mounted
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
Attributed to the Saint Louis Glassworks (French, f. 1767)
Of ovoid form, the glasses canted and with flared necks and bases, supported by scrolling ormolu mounts to the sides and bases
Lithyalin glass is an opaque or translucent marbled glass with a surface resembling polished gemstones in a wide range of colours. It was first made by the chemist Friedrich Egermann (Bohemian, 1777-1864) in 1828 in northern Bohemia, and he patented the process in 1829. When this patent expired, similar pieces were made in France, Bohemia, China and Russia.
item.excerpt:encoded: These splendid antique vases are a rare example of fine Lithyalin glass used over a large surface area, making the pair an exclusive collectable.

item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded: After the model by J.J. Kaendler, with a relief naval scene, flanked by figures of Neptune, a mermaid and galloping horses, the circular flaring base with spouting dolphins among bulrushes, the underside with under glaze blue crossed swords mark above one cancellation line, incised model number 320 and impressed numerals.
item.excerpt:encoded: This exquisite Meissen porcelain ewer, representative of 'water', was created as part of a series of four ewers, each symbolising a different element.

item.title: Ormolu mounted sevres
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded: The dark blue ground body painted to the front with playful and amorous pastoral scenes, decorated throughout with gilt rocaille motif, mounted with twin ormolu handles shaped as winged classical female busts, surmounted by a shaped bulbous cover topped with an ormolu presentoir filled with fruit, raised on three hoof feet standing on a shaped triform base with toupie feet.
item.excerpt:encoded: This exquisite Svres style French porcelain vase is decorated with scenes of pastoral idyll, examples of both beauty and serenity.

item.title: porcelain vases
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
The ormolu French, late 19th Century by Henri Vian (French, 1860-1905); the porcelain Chinese, early 18th Century, Kangxi period.
Each of baluster form decorated with a procession of a figure on horseback with attendants in gardens and an immortal hovering on a cloud with a baby above a bridge, the ormolu signed 'h. Vian'.
item.excerpt:encoded: The porcelain of these fine antique vases dates to the Chinese Kangxi period, and is notable for the high quality detailing of its narrative scenes.

item.title: japanese amari porcelain vases
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded: Decorated throughout with floral patterns; the porcelain Japanese, c.1700, the ormolu French, 19th Century.
item.excerpt:encoded: These stunning antique Japanese vases are examples of exceptionally high quality Imari porcelain ware, which is renowned for its beauty and craftsmanship

item.title: krated shaped vase
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
The Medici shaped vase on a square gilt base, the upper part curved outwards with twin gilt handles, the front painted with an outdoor scene of men hunting on their horses accompanied by their hunting dogs, additionally decorated with raised gilt detailing of wreaths of foliage and pattern-work on a green ground
The underside with blue KPM sceptre mark
item.excerpt:encoded: This impressive vase pays homage to the Medici family, rulers of Renaissance Florence, who highly prized vases inspired by the ancient krater form

item.title: Pair of ormolu mounted sevres
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded: On blue ground, the front with scenes depicting putti in clouds within gilt borders
item.excerpt:encoded: An elegant duo, the opulence of these fine antique French vases will enhance the dcor of any setting, be it a public or a private space

item.title: Seventeen piece paris
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
Comprising twelve plates, two low tazze, one tall tazza and two sauce tureens and covers, all painted with flowers within turquoise and gilt borders, most pieces stamped to the underside 'Ed. Honor / Paris'.
Sauce tureens height 15cm, width 25cm, depth 17cm
Tall tazza height 10.5cm, diameter 23cm
Low tazze height 4.5cm, diameter 22.5cm
Plates height 2.5cm, diameter 22.5cm
item.excerpt:encoded: This impressive set is an excellent example of Honor's high quality porcelain work, which was a favourite among contemporary European aristocracy

item.title: sixteen piece dessert service
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
Comprising one tazze, four comports and eleven plates, each depicting birds among floral branches on ivory ground within stylised borders.
Diameter of all pieces 24cm; height of tazze 12cm; height of comports 6cm; height of plates 3cm
item.excerpt:encoded: Crafted by prestigious English maker Royal Crown Derby, this exquisite antique dessert service would make an elegant addition to any fine dining room.

item.title: Collectable parcel gilt porcelain
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded: Circular porcelain plate, blue ground with articulated gilded rim, the centre painted with two peasants in a landscape
item.excerpt:encoded: The narrative scene on this fine antique plate encapsulates the preoccupation with the labouring man, prevalent in 19th century Russian artwork.

item.title: Cabinet plate
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
The raised gilt leaf scrollwork border on an ivory and green background, surrounding a painting of the Madonna & Child after Raphael
With underglazed blue crown mark to the reverse and gilded inscription 'Madonna von Raphael Santio, Original in der Dresdener Jemaldegalleri'
item.excerpt:encoded: This elegant antique porcelain plate depicts a touching image of the Madonna holding the Christ Child, both of whom gaze out into the distance.

item.title: plate painted with a view of riga
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded: Circular porcelain plate with painted scene, the landscape within a viridian green border with gilt decor.
item.excerpt:encoded: This fine antique plate illustrates a view of Riga, the capital of Lativa, as it would have appeared at the beginning of the 19th century.

item.title: Matched pairn
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded: After a design by Hughes Protat, the circular bodies modelled as a barrel with entwined grapevine handles, the shoulders each applied with four Bacchic putti.
item.excerpt:encoded: These charming antique ewers are an excellent example of fine Victorian majolica ware, which the British ceramic manufacturer Minton was famous for.

item.title: Enamelled glass
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
Consisting of one jug with stopper and six glasses, in the Islamic style.
Jug with stopper: height 19 cm; diameter 20 cm Glasses: height 6.8 cm; width 10 cm; depth 5.5 cm
item.excerpt:encoded: This iridescent glass liqueur set is distinctly and impressively detailed, typifying the quality of glass produced by the Moser factory in Bohemia.

item.title: Acid etches ewer bu baccarat
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded: Of baluster form, decorated in blue with herons on a riverbank amidst bullrushes and trees, with a star cut base
item.excerpt:encoded: The delicate blue etching on this fine antique ewer is offset beautifully by the surrounding frosted glass, resulting in a wonderful visual contrast.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: good

item.title: The succsessfull suitor
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
Depicting a lavish interior scene with the chosen suitor being introduced to his future wife; oil on canvas in a carved giltwood frame, signed lower right 'Arturo Ricci'.
Canvas height 63.5cm, width 88cm
Frame height 84cm, width 108cm, depth 7cm
item.excerpt:encoded: This exceptional antique oil painting, portraying the romantic scene in breathtaking detail and stunning naturalism, is one of Ricci's finest works.

item.title: Noise in the classroom
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
left 'R. Geyling'.
Frame height 93cm, width 126cm; canvas height 66cm, width 99cm
item.excerpt:encoded: This charming antique oil painting captures a moment of high spirited classroom fun, as the girls play mischievously in the absence of their teacher.

item.title: Pair of allegorical oil paintings
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded: Depicting two of the five senses: Sound and Taste- Sound as a female figure draped in robes holding a tambourine in her raised left hand with a cherub by her side seated on a garland of flowers and playing the bagpipes decorated with a further garland of flowers to the upper left corner and flowers below; Taste as a male figure draped in robes holding a glass of wine in his right hand and a sceptre in his left hand with a cherub in front of him holding a garland of flowers in his raised left hand and a jug in his lowered right hand decorated with a further garland of flowers to the upper right corner, a vine with grapes through the centre and flowers below.
item.excerpt:encoded: These fine oil paintings are a brilliant example of Cornicelius' figurative work, portraying Classically inspired personifications of the senses.

item.title: plaque depicting the virgin mary
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
After the painting by Bartolom Esteban Murillo (Spanish, 1618-1682) 'The Immaculate Conception of the Venerable Ones', 1678; housed in the Museo del Prado, Madrid, Spain.
Depicting the Virgin Mary in blue and white; surrounded by winged cherubs.
item.excerpt:encoded: The delicate naturalism of this fine antique porcelain plaque is evident in the gentle expression on the Virgin's face, which calmly gazes upwards.

item.title: Porcelain plaque
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded: This fine Meissen porcelain plaque is exceptional for its quality of naturalism, exhibiting figures that are depicted with the utmost precision.
item.excerpt:encoded:
After 'The Ascension of Christ' altarpiece, c. 1750 in Dresden Cathedral, by Anton Raphael Mengs (German, 1728-1779).
The reverse with underglaze blue crossed sword marks and scratch mark '1130'.
